Downloading Node.js
1. Go to https://nodejs.org/en/download/
2. Select Windows Installer
3. Download package

Installing Haskell
1. Go to https://www.haskell.org/ghcup/guide/#certificate-authority-errors-curl
2. Copy the code at the bottom
    It should be like the line below, if not exactly the same
Set-ExecutionPolicy Bypass -Scope Process -Force;[System.Net.ServicePointManager]::SecurityProtocol = [System.Net.ServicePointManager]::SecurityProtocol -bor 3072;Invoke-Command -ScriptBlock ([ScriptBlock]::Create((Invoke-WebRequest https://www.haskell.org/ghcup/sh/bootstrap-haskell.ps1 -UseBasicParsing))) -ArgumentList $true,$false,$false,$false,$false,$false,$false,"","","","",$true
3. Open Windows Powershell
    Can be run as user or admin, doesn't really matter
4. Paste the code and run it
5. Wait for the code to finish running. This could take quite a while

Installing Stack
1. Go to https://docs.haskellstack.org/en/stable/#how-to-install-stack
2. Select Windows
3. Click on the embedded Windows Installer link
4. Download the installer
5. Open File Explorer and run the installer (application) to install stack

Checking Environment Variables (and their values)
1. Go to the search bar next to the Start button
2. Search for "Edit the system environment variables" and select it
3. Click on environment variables on the window that popped up
4. The new window will show all Environment Variables and their values
